Welcome
At Printpack, we are industry leaders in flexible and specialty rigid packaging. We combine your vision with our unique capabilities, knowledge of consumer trends, and a wide range of product offerings in a variety of markets to enhance your brand and drive success. We’re proud to say that our advanced printing methods and extensive manufacturing and converting capabilities have garnered many accolades over the years that take your business to new levels.
So have a look around and see what all the fuss is about.

We are having a blast at the Georgia World Congress Center in Atlanta this week at the PMMI Skills USA TECHSPO event, the largest trade show for technical education.

SkillsUSA TECHSPO is an opportunity for students to engage directly with partners from industry and education. More than 6,500 outstanding career and technical education students – all state contest winners – compete hands-on in different trade, technical and leadership fields.

If you are at the event today, tomorrow, and Thursday, stop by our booth to speak to Katie Harris and Mallory Tredway about what we do in the packaging industry. You can even spin the wheel for a prize or snack and answer our packaging trivia! For more information about this event, head here: @skillsusa

#PrintpackProud #FlexiblePackaging #SkillsUSA

Wish-cycling is the act of tossing something in your recycling bin with the hope that it is recyclable, without really knowing if it is or not. It is also known as aspirational recycling. To combat this, we take leading CPG brands` packaging from wishful thinking to truly sustainable. To do this, we guide brands to the proper packaging solution recommendations with researched consumer insights. Learn more about our #sustainablepackaging process and head to our website.

#PrintpackPreserve #SustainablePackaging #Circularity

We are making waves – that is, #sustainablepackaging waves, for our oceans! 🌊

We design packaging for optimal end-of-life so that we can help consumers divert plastic waste from landfills as well as our oceans. The ability to recycle packaging after use is important to consumers. In fact, 76% of consumers say they try to act in a way that is not harmful to the environment (Source: Mintel). We also continue to explore solutions for limiting greenhouse gas and source reduction. #shellyeah! ♻️

#WorldOceanDay #30x30 #PrintpackPreserve

Circularity is in our blood – or should we say in our packaging?! Our goal is to reduce emissions, minimize waste, and consume fewer natural resources when making our packaging. With our Printpack Preserve™ product line, we focus on using renewable, bio-based materials and post-consumer recycled content to reduce the carbon footprint of a package from the start.

#BeatPlasticPollution #PrintpackPreserve #SustainablePackaging #Circularity #WorldEnvironmentDay

Do you know what motivates sustainable packaging professionals the most? Having reliable, sustainable packaging solutions for leading consumer packaged goods.

♻️ We are proud to announce our development of Preserve® Fiber recyclable flexible packaging. The fiber-based structures are PFAS and PVDC-free, designed to pass Western Michigan University (WMU) FBA OCC Repulpability and Recyclability protocols, and are eligible for the How2Recycle® “Widely Recycled” label for curbside recyclability.

🌎Read more and head to our website (link in bio).

#PrintpackPreserve #PaperPackaging #SustainablePackaging

Today is the first day of SPC Impact in Austin, TX. If you are at the show this week, be sure to add tomorrow’s panel discussion, “Sustainable Packaging from Concept to Commercialization” to your agenda from 11:00 AM – 11:45 AM CDT.

Join the discussion with our subject matter experts Megan Robison, Sr. Product Stewardship Engineer and Madison Keller, Product Development Engineer along with speakers from Tetra Pak and ProAmpac. Together, the panel will highlight best practices for a successful sustainable packaging project as well as what they have learned about earning the buy-in of all stakeholders to make a sustainable packaging project a reality.

Most love a good #ThrowbackThursday. Especially when it’s about the Earth. 🌎

Sustainability is a #packagingtrend that continues to gain momentum. #SustainablePackaging was a top trend in 2021 and continues to be top of mind for consumers AND brands in 2023. As many CPG brands ramp up to meet the 2025 sustainability deadline, consumers are expecting more transparency. In fact, around 34% of consumers believe brands should be required to use labeling that shows the environmental impact of the product/package. Source: Mintel
